object.script:
function onTick() resource = property.getText("resource") level = input.getNumber(1) is_out = input.getBool(1) is_in = input.getBool(2) end
function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(128, 128, 128) screen.setColor(128, 128, 128) screen.drawTextBox(2, 2, w-4, h-4, resource .. " storage", 0, -1) screen.drawTextBox(2, 2, w-4, h-4, "level:", -1, 0) screen.drawTextBox(2, 2, w-4, h-4, string.format("%.0f", level) .. " L", 1, 0)
if level < 1 then screen.setColor(255, 16, 0) screen.drawTextBox(2, 2, w-4, h-4, "empty", 0, 1) elseif is_out then screen.setColor(96, 96, 0) screen.drawTextBox(2, 2, w-4, h-4, "pumping out", 0, 1) elseif is_in then screen.setColor(96, 96, 0) screen.drawTextBox(2, 2, w-4, h-4, "pumping in", 0, 1) else screen.setColor(64, 255, 0) screen.drawTextBox(2, 2, w-4, h-4, "ready", 0, 1) end
end
